description.text:
### Tested versions

4.4, 4.5

### System information

Linux

### Issue description

Shader built-in `VIEWPORT_SIZE` is affected by `scaling_3d_scale`:
```gdshader
shader_type spatial;

render_mode cull_front, unshaded, depth_draw_never;

uniform vec3 outline_color : source_color = vec3(0.2);
uniform float outline_width : hint_range(0.0, 10.0, 0.001) = 4.0;

void vertex() {
	vec4 clip_position = PROJECTION_MATRIX * MODELVIEW_MATRIX * vec4(VERTEX, 1.0);
	vec3 clip_normal = mat3(PROJECTION_MATRIX) * mat3(MODELVIEW_MATRIX) * NORMAL;

	clip_position.xy += normalize(clip_normal.xy) / VIEWPORT_SIZE * clip_position.w * outline_width;
	POSITION = clip_position;
}

void fragment() {
	ALBEDO = outline_color.rgb;
}
```
https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b1f06db8-dfcf-419e-bf49-577811180855

If I hardcode the viewport size instead of using `VIEWPORT_SIZE`, the outline size will not be affected by `scaling_3d_scale`

### Steps to reproduce

Open the MRP and change `scaling_3d_scale`.

